@node History "History:-"

@{u}@{b}QuickBrowser History file:-@{uu}@{ub}

ALPHA 0.1  * 14th April 1998 - Passed my driving test today... Wahey!! :)))

* The first running version of QuickBrowser

ALPHA 0.2 * 14th April 1998

* Made the window as a appwindow so files can be dropped and then read.
* Added normal menus
* Added the main navigation buttons.

ALPHA 0.3 * 15th April 1998

* Sorted out the userdata for the navigation buttons so information about the
  button is shown in the status text box.
* Fixed a lame bug which made QuickBrowser crash if the Warning window is asked
  to be opened.

BETA 0.4 * 16th April 1998

* Got the Open menu item to work. An ASL window appears asking for a file.
* The goto string now returns the filename inputted from the ASL requester.
* Added the about window..
* Upped the stack to 8192, as every small MUI application should be. :)
* Made the MUI prefs Menuitem to work.
* Made the about MUI menuitem to work.

BETA 0.5 * Early morning 17th April 1998

* ASL now works correctly. Select a file and see it load! :)
* Added .htm pattern to ASL requester.

BETA 0.6 * 18th April 1998.

* Fixed the bug which zaps around 15meg of memory when QuickBrowser is run.
* The title of the document is now displayed on the main QuickBrowser window title.
* Fixed a bug which creeped into the appwindow notification mechanism.
* Fixed the lame bug which didn't allow you to have a path bigger than 4 characters
  in the "choose default directory" in prefrences window.
* I don't know if you have found this out with using V0.5, but I found that QuickBrowser
  didn't try/bother loading images. Well it does now. :)
* Fixed a bug which didn't allow any filenames typed into the main string gadget 
  in the main QuickBrowser to be loaded correctly.
* Home button now works.
* Somehow loading and saving of stringadgets didn't work correctly. Reverted back to
  normal MUI string gadgets from Textinput for now.
  
BETA 0.62 * 21st April 1998.

* Better handling of prefrences.. I have added three save and load related menuitems
  which I have implemented.
* Added small text object to main startup window. It tells what is happening on startup
  like "loading configuration file" etc.
  
INTERNAL BETA 0.63 * 25th April 1998.

* Implemented "show source" window.
* Added external editor button and got it working!

INTERNAL BETA 0.64 * 26th April 1998

* Changed the show source textspace to texteditor class so source can be changed, updated
  and save.
* Added "select external editor" prefrences stringadget.
* Added "show status bar as infotext?" checkmark in prefrences window.
* Added document information window.

TESTERS BETA 0.65 * 30th April 1998

* Added document title, size and dir to doc info window.
* Added toolbar prefs to prefrences window - not correctly implemented yet. (Disabled)
* Prefrences window is split into four register groups, main, windows, paths and Misc.
* General cleanup of prefrences window layout such as correct weights to
  different objects.
* Added reset button to source window... and it works! :)
* Added update button.

TESTERS BETA 0.66 * 9th May 1998

* Got the show doc info and show source windows to open at startup if the
  corresponding checkmark's are true.
  
TESTERS BETA 0.67 * 10th May 1998
  
* Better handling of startup of QuickBrowser. Windows opened in correct order.

PUBLIC BETA 0.68 * 11th May 1998

* Been working on the toolbar for the view source window. Only 20% complete now :-/
* Added *buggy* CLI support so you can run QuickBrowser through CLI + with adding
  a argument. Please note that this feature will probably (almost certain) will
  disable the "Home html file feature".

Bug report:-

        I know that when you, the user will run this new version of QuickBrowser, that the
file info and view source window will also appear! Don't get pissed off, the windows will not
popup if you disable them on the "Startup Windows" section of the preferences.

@endnode

@node Toolbars "Creating your own Toolbars:-"

        As you probably already know, you can edit the toolbar to your own 
presonal taste via the prefrences. Also, you can use a Graphics editing program 
to create your own toolbar!

@{u}@{b}How to did it?@{ub}@{uu}

yrttrhhirgh

@{b}@{u}Rewards:-@{ub}@{uu}

	Besides self-pride, if you create a decent looking toolbar, I will be more than 
happy to
include it into the main Graphics Kit archive for future releases. Also you will get a 
mention in the
main program and docs too! :)

@endnode

@node Registration "It's freeware!"

QuickBrowser is Freeware for the moment, and it will probably stay freeware for a while.
After QuickBrowser V1 will be released, I hope that I can work towards V2 which will be
shareware. QuickBrowser V2 will probably be a part of the Power Accounts professional
package when it is released.	
        
@endnode

